thread.title: AerCap sells 17 aircraft in third quarter
thread.title_full: AerCap sells 17 aircraft in third quarter

author: flightglobal.com
title: AerCap sells 17 aircraft in third quarter
text:
AerCap signed lease agreements for 46 aircraft, including 12 widebody and 34 narrowbody aircraft, during the third quarter of this year.
The lessor executed sale and part-out transactions for 17 aircraft, and acquired seven units, including a Boeing 787-8, a 787-9, and five 737-800s.
The sold aircraft covered two Airbus A320s, four A330-200s, a single A340-300, two Boeing 757-200s, a pair of 777-200ERs and two 777-300ERs from its owned portfolio, and one A321-200, one 737 classic, one 757-200 and one MD-83 from AerCap's managed portfolio.
As of the end of September, AerCap's portfolio consists of over 1,700 aircraft that were either owned, managed, or under contract to purchase.
